tspan.tspan: Player #1 Hand
Player #2 Hand
Life Tokens on Cards
Discard
Point at any card. Move it into the
DISCARD pile if it isn't there already.
Name a card from the DISCARD/
UNUSED piles. If that card is present,
add it to your hand.
"Yes, yes, yes! Can I tell you, this is the
greatest moment of my life? I promise,
promise that I won't set anything on fire.
You have my word on that! This is great!"
Blithering Fool
If your opponent plays an ability where
you end up LOSING any card *other*
than Old Coot, point at a card. You may
take as many life tokens from that card as
you would like and place them into your
life token pool.
x1 - Organ Failure
Remove as many life tokens from your
opponent's pool as there are life tokens on
ALL of your cards. Remove the life tokens
you used to damage your opponent from
play.
"Wait, what?"
Old Coot
Point at a card. That card
cannot be
USED or LOST
until the start of your
next turn.
x2 - Terrible Idea
Point at a card, and reveal it. You may
choose one ability from that card to play
for yourself.
You must additionally pay
the
associated life token
cost with that
ability from the life tokens on this card.
"This is just like the battle of... um. Hold
on, I'll get there in a second."
Overeager Tactician
Point at a card. Remove any number of
life tokens on that card, and place half of
those tokens (rounded down) on a card of
your choice. Place the remainder tokens
in your life pool.
Remove 4 life tokens from your
opponent's pool.
"I'm a better at swords than Benedict ever
was, you stupid jerks!"
Egomaniacal Fencer
If you swap cards with your opponent,
you each remove half as many life tokens
from your pools as there are life tokens on
the card that each of you have been given.
Keep the life tokens on the cards after
SWAPping.
x3 - Tax Evasion
Point at a card. SWAP that card with any
card in your hand.
"Everything is 100% legit, trust me."
Fraudulent Accountant
If your opponent plays an ability where
you end up LOSING this card, remove
twice as many life tokens from your
opponent's pool as there are life tokens on
this card. Keep the life tokens on this
card.
x2 - Runcible Spoon
Name a card. If your opponent has that
card in your hand, they must show it to
you.
"I am a SORCERER of the weirding ways.
Best me if you... wait! Pick another card."
Muddled Magician
Point at 3 cards that are NOT in the
discard pile. Your opponent must pick
ONE to go into the discard pile.
Name a card. If your opponent has that
card, they must EITHER: Pay 4 life tokens
to keep it, or SWAP it for this card.
"I promise I can handle it, honest! Just...
don't trust me with anything important."
Rebellious Youth
If your opponent flips a card face-up with
at least four life tokens, you may discard
one card from the cards you own.
x1 - Honk
Remove as many life tokens from this card
as you would like, and place them on one
of your opponent's cards.
"HONK!"
Horn Guy
DISCARD up to 3 cards from the cards
you
own.
You must skip your turn for as
many
times as you discarded cards.
x2 - It's Nothing
Point at 2 cards and place them side by side
face-down. Do not shuffle them. Your
opponent must pick ONE to take. You
take the other.
"There's no problem with the castle walls!
I'm out there everyday and I see nothing."
Bumbling Patroller
If this card is front-facing on the start of
your turn, flip it face-down. Your
opponent loses as many life tokens as
cards they did NOT USE last turn.
Keep this card front-facing after your turn
ends.
"I'll deal with it later."
Useless Underminer
x3 - Disheartening Service
Point at up to 4 cards that you do not own,
and add them to your hand. For each card
you've drawn, gain 2 temporary life
tokens; they are removed after you have
played all your abilities, before you take
damage based on the number of cards you
own.
"The title of the sermon is: God is dead.
Don't give me that look, Clara."
Impious Pretender
If your opponent ever invokes a
REACTion, remove as many life tokens
from your opponent's pool as there are life
tokens on this card. This invokes AFTER
your opponent's REACTion is resolved.
Keep the life tokens on this card.
x4 - Hangover
Name a card. If that card is NOT in the
discard, add it to your hand.
"This calls for a celebratory drink!"
Devious Drunkard
